\b \cf0 The TX Modular System - Audio Setup Window\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf0 \
When the TX Modular System is started, the 
\b Audio Setup
\b0  window is displayed first. This is where you configure your audio settings, before starting the audio engine.\
The controls are as follows:\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\b \cf0 Start Audio Engine button
\b0  - this will start the engine and display the main TX Modular System window. Only press this once you have set the options for your audio device - see below.\
\

\b Quit button
\b0  - This quits the TX Modular System completely.\
\

\b Audio Device For Input and Output
\b0  - This sets the audio device that will be used for audio input & output to & from the the TX Modular System. \
- If you set this to Use Default, it will use the default device for your computer. To check or change the default audio device, run 
\b Audio MIDI Setup
\b0  which can be found in the folder: 
\b Applications/ Utilities
\b0 . Select on the 
\b Audio Devices
\b0  window and see which device is marked with symbols for sound input and output.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\i\b \cf0 Note: 
\i0\b0  You won't be able to start the audio engine if you select 
\i built-in microphone
\i0 , 
\i built-in input
\i0 , or 
\i built-in output
\i0  as the Audio Device because they aren't valid as inputs 
\i and
\i0  outputs (they are just one or the other). To use your built-in microphone or built-in input for input and your built-in output for output, you need to first create a virtual "aggregate" device using 
\b Audio MIDI Setup
\b0 . (See notes below).\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\b \cf0 Audio Device Sample Rate
\b0  - If you set this to Use Default, it will use the default settings for the device. If you change it to another value, make sure it is valid for that device.\
\

\b Audio Device Buffer Size
\b0  - If you set this to Use Default, it will use the default settings for the device. If you change it to another value, make sure it is valid for that device. \
\

