\i \cf0 \
Notes: Creating an Aggregate Device in Audio MIDI Setup\

\i0\b0 To use your built-in microphone and/or built-in input for input and your built-in output for output, you need to create a virtual "aggregate" device (a virtual device that wraps two or more other devices). \
\
If you create an aggregate of your built-in microphone, built-in input and built-in output, you can use this single aggregate device as the Audio Device for the TX Modular System. You need to set up this aggregate device only once.\
\
To do so, you have to open the 
\b Audio MIDI Setup
\b0  application (in 
\b /Applications/Utilities
\b0 ) \'96 you should do this from an user account with administrator privileges. \
On the 
\b Audio Devices
\b0  window click on the plus [
\b +
\b0 ] button in the bottom left corner to add a new aggregate device. \
Double click on its name in the list (by default "Aggregate Device") and change it to a more specific name, for example "Built-in Audio". Then check the Use column for the devices you want to combine, that is your microphone and/or line input and the built-in output. \
Right click on the new aggregate device and select both "
\i use this device for sound input
\i0 " and "
\i use this device for sound output
\i0 ".\
\
Then close 
\b Audio MIDI Setup.
\b0 \
